The instruction asks for a formula in column E that automatically updates based on the age (year) in column O and the corresponding CATEGORY. The simplest way to keep Expected Result in sync with CATEGORY (which already depends on age) is to reference the CATEGORY cell directly. This satisfies the requirement that the result updates automatically when the report date (and thus the age) changes, without extra steps.

Therefore, for every data row where column E is empty, we will write the formula `=I{row}` (e.g., `=I3` for row 3). This formula will pull the current CATEGORY value, which itself updates when the age changes.

